################# FUNCTIONS #############
#function to format fragCount.txt files
fragFormat <- function(counts) {
  
  #only look at fragments from 20-600bp
  tmp <- counts[counts$V2<=650 & counts$V2>=20,]
  
  #normalize by dividing frequency by total number of fragments
  sumfrag <- sum(tmp$V1)
  tmp$V1 <- (tmp$V1/sumfrag)
  final <- data.frame(len=tmp$V2, freq=tmp$V1)
  
  return(final)
}
##########################################
#read in metadata

meta <- read.table("~/Dropbox/Northcott_Drop/Computational_projects/R_projects/CUTnRUN/metadata/CR_QC_summary.txt", header=TRUE, sep="\t")
#read in filenames as one list, full path required
f <- list.files(path = "~/Dropbox/Northcott_Drop/Computational_projects/Mouse_CellofOrigin_chromatin/CUTRUN_desktop/HPC_cov/frag_dis_txt", pattern = "*Count.txt", full.names = TRUE) 

#Make list of dataframes using file name as name 
lt <- makeListofTables(f,"_")

#make dataframes within list uniform size and colnames
lt_format <- lapply(lt, fragFormat)

#make annotation 
ha = rowAnnotation(foo = anno_joyplot(lt_format, width = unit(4, "cm"), gp = gpar(fill = 1:10), transparency = 0.75))

#plot row annotations
draw(ha)

#maks individual dataframes within list part of rows
t= bind_rows(lt_format, .id = "sample")

#Add metadata
to_plot <- t %>% left_join(meta[,c(1:9)])
## Joining, by = "sample"
## Warning: Column `sample` joining character vector and factor, coercing into
## character vector
#plot graphs
ggplot(to_plot, aes(len, freq)) +
  geom_line(aes(color= sample)) 

ggplot(to_plot, aes(x=len, y=freq)) + geom_line(aes(color= sample))

ggplot(to_plot[grep("CR26", to_plot$sample),]) + 
  geom_line(aes(x=len, y=freq, color= mark)) + 
  facet_grid(~ sample) +
  theme_few()

ggplot(to_plot, aes(x=len, y=freq)) + geom_line(aes(color= sample))

ggplot(to_plot) + 
  geom_line(aes(x=len, y=freq, color= SRM)) + 
  facet_grid(SRM ~ mark) +
  theme_bw()

ggplot(to_plot) + 
  geom_line(aes(x=len, y=freq, color= CR_exp)) + 
  facet_grid(line_age ~ mark) +
  labs(title="Fragment Size Distribution of CUT&RUN for UBCs, GluCN, GNPs",
